==English==
===Etymology===
From the Greek ''equi'' (equal) and [[areal]].
===Adjective===
'''equiareal'''

#{{cartography}} Describing a [[map]] with the property of being equal-area; thus a circle of the constant [[radius]], located anywhere on the map, covers the same area on the mapped surface.  Also called equivalent, [[homolographic]], [[homalographic]], [[authalic]], equiareal.

*The most commonly used term for this property is equal-area.